    "plan_content": "Here's my implementation plan for `uv cache stats`:\n\n---\n\n## What I found\n\nAfter exploring the codebase, the pattern is well-established and consistent. Here's what maps directly onto the new command:\n\n- **`crates/uv-cache/src/lib.rs`** — `CacheBucket::iter()` yields 10 buckets (excludes `Python`). `Cache::bucket(bucket) -> PathBuf` gives the path. `Display for CacheBucket` formats as e.g. `\"wheels-v6\"`.\n- **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_size.rs`** — uses `DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` and `human_readable_bytes(n) -> (f64, &str)`. The new command mirrors this exactly, just per-bucket.\n- **`cache_size`** has a `Preview` gate — the new `cache_stats` does **not** need one per the requirements.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary (4 touch-points)\n\n### 1. `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`\n- Append `/// Show per-bucket cache statistics.\\nStats(StatsArgs),` inside `CacheCommand` after `Size(SizeArgs)`\n- Add `StatsArgs` struct (identical shape to `SizeArgs`) after it\n\n### 2. **New file** `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`\n- `pub(crate) fn cache_stats(cache: &Cache, human_readable: bool, printer: Printer) -> Result<ExitStatus>`\n- Loop over `CacheBucket::iter()`, call `DiskUsage` on `cache.bucket(bucket)`, guard with `.exists()`, accumulate total, print `{bucket}: {size}` per line, then `total: {size}`\n\n### 3. `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`\n- Add `mod cache_stats;` (after `mod cache_size;`, line 84)\n- Add `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;` (after `cache_size` re-export, line 21)\n\n### 4. `crates/uv/src/lib.rs`\n- Add match arm for `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` immediately after the `Size` arm (line 1181), calling `commands::cache_stats(&cache, args.human, printer)`",
